description: Creates a container for a collection of data being ingested for analysis. The dataset contains the metadata describing where the data is and what the data actually looks like. For example, it contains the location of the data source, the data schema, and other information. A dataset also contains any tags associated with the ingested data.

parameters.name: DatasetName
parameters.description: The name of the dataset being created.

parameters.name: DatasetSchema
parameters.description: A JSON description of the data that is in each time series dataset, including names, column names, and data types. InlineDataSchema (string) --- The data schema used within the given dataset.

nested_params.name: InlineDataSchema
nested_params.description: The data schema used within the given dataset.

parameters.name: ClientToken
parameters.description: A unique identifier for the request. If you do not set the client request token, Amazon Lookout for Equipment generates one. This field is autopopulated if not provided.

parameters.name: Tags
parameters.description: Any tags associated with the ingested data described in the dataset. (dict) --- A tag is a key-value pair that can be added to a resource as metadata. The key for the specified tag. The value for the specified tag.

nested_params.name: Key
nested_params.description: The key for the specified tag.

nested_params.name: Value
nested_params.description: The value for the specified tag.

nested_items.name: DatasetName
nested_items.description: The name of the dataset being created.

nested_items.name: DatasetArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the dataset being created.

nested_items.name: Status
nested_items.description: Indicates the status of the CreateDataset operation.
